This is a simple web application.

Library and framework:

1. Server: Node.js + Express + Passportjs
2. Client: AngularJS + Bootstrap
3. Database: PostgreSQL

4. ORM: Sequelize (for PostgreSQL)
5. Task Runner: grunt 
6. Test Frontend: Karma + Jasmine
7. Test and debug Backend: Morgan + node-inspector

How to run:
1. install PostgreSQL : http://postgresapp.com

2. create your database with name: note_app
This name was config in : config/database.js

2. make sure you are in application folder.
 Download all library: npm install

3. install grunt task runner cli : npm install -g grunt-cli

4. install test karma cli: npm install -g karma-cli

5. now you can start server: grunt server
go to : http://localhost:3000

6. if you want to run test karma: grunt test